##
## Upstream tests to disable
##
## When adding a new filter to this list, please include a short description of
## why the filter is required and create an associated tracking issue.
##

# These only fail in Static x86 build, but pass in Release. The test crashes a
# utility process on purpose and is supposed to continue after the crash, but
# it seems in Static build the crash isn't detected/handled.
-CDM_10/ECKEncryptedMediaTest.MultipeCdmTypes/0
-CDM_11/ECKEncryptedMediaTest.MultipeCdmTypes/0

# These tests fail on x86 CI but pass locally
-MetricIntegrationTest.LargestContentfulPaint_SubframeInput
-SaveDesktopSnapshotTest.SaveDesktopSnapshot

# These screen-capture / media-stream tests crash on x86 with a NOTREACHED in
# base::win::AssertComInitialized. WebRTC's window capturer calls
# CoCreateInstance on a thread-pool worker without COM initialization, which the
# DCheckedCoCreateInstance hook fatally enforces.
-CaptureHandleBrowserTest.*
-CapturedSurfaceControl*.*
-*DisplayMedia*.*
-SubCapture*.*
-WebRtcScreenCaptureBrowserTestUserRejection.*

# These PDF JS tests time out (32 s) on x86.
-All/PDFExtensionJSTest.*/*
-All/PDFExtensionPacificTimeZoneJSTest.*
-*PDFExtension*SaveToDrive*.*

-ExtensionCspApiTest.ServiceWorkerIsConstrainedByMV3CSPEvenIfSandboxed
-PageLoadMetricsBrowserTestTerminatedPage.UkmIsRecordedWhenRenderProcessShutsDown
-PasswordChangeUIControllerBrowserTest.PageIsInteractableWhileToastIsShowing
